prompt:
Our print-shop order intake exchanges one JSON envelope for three job kinds, and the current parser is a hand-rolled switch over a 'kind' string that builds Maps — every schema tweak breaks it somewhere else. I want it on Jackson's polymorphic databind. The pom is already set up for the build (leave the existing pins alone) but has no JSON library yet: add com.fasterxml.jackson.core:jackson-databind, pinned exactly at 2.22.1 (transitives come along on their own).

Model it in package com.inkbarrel.printspec. JobSpec is the base type, carrying the 'kind' discriminator as a JSON property; the three payloads are records CardsJob, BannerJob, BookletJob with these wire shapes (field order on the wire is contractual — the fulfillment vendor diffs raw payloads, so serialization must be byte-for-byte):
- kind 'cards': {"kind":"cards","orderRef":"ORD-2101","stockName":"pearl 350gsm","quantity":500,"cornersRounded":false}
- kind 'banner': {"kind":"banner","orderRef":"ORD-2107","widthCm":180,"heightCm":60,"grommets":true}
- kind 'booklet': {"kind":"booklet","orderRef":"ORD-2112","pages":24,"staplePattern":"saddle"}
Dimensions/quantity/pages are ints, grommets/cornersRounded booleans, the rest strings.

Behavior on a plain default-configured ObjectMapper (the intake service constructs `new ObjectMapper()` — no custom config, so the model annotations have to do all the work): 'kind' is accepted anywhere in the object when reading but always leads when writing; a list read through a TypeReference<List<JobSpec>> and written back via mapper.writerFor(that same TypeReference) comes out byte-identical — the intake service writes lists through writerFor because type erasure would otherwise drop the discriminator; an unrecognized kind or an absent kind fails with InvalidTypeIdException (typeId 'poster' surfaces on the exception, absent kind gives a null typeId); an unexpected field like 'laminate' fails with UnrecognizedPropertyException naming the property. src/test/java/com/inkbarrel/printspec/JobWireTest.java is the contract — don't edit it. Done when `mvn -q test` passes; fetching the pinned jackson artifacts from Maven Central on first build is expected.
